⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Genly Ai
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Genly Ai:U1:1673e4⟧

WHO   — Genly Ai — the lone envoy who crossed the Ice
WHAT  — The narrator of The Left Hand of Darkness — the lone envoy who fails in the courts of kings, is broken in a labor camp, and is saved by hauling a sledge across eight hundred miles of ice with the one Gethenian who believed him.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Hainish Cycle  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Ekumen comes not to conquer but to ask; because trust must be offered by a single unarmed man so a world is never coerced; because to know another you must first unlearn the certainties of your own kind — including the certainty of gender.
HOW   — By patience and peril, by the slow undoing of his Terran assumptions, by surviving Pulefen Farm, and above all by the crossing of the Gobrin Ice with Estraven — where need and shism gave way at last to love.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I came alone, unarmed, to ask — and it was on the ice, with the one I could not understand, that I finally saw a human being.

